title: For Sale/Trade:  Milled SKS w/ Blade Bayonet (MAUI)
postcontent:
This is a really nice rifle. 7.62x39 (AK-47) caliber. Semi-automatic with fixed 10 round magazine (included) or removable 20-40rd magazines (not included, but legal). Beautiful stainless steel fold out blade bayonet. Almost all of these rifles you see will have an ugly black spike for a bayonet, but these early Sino-Soviet models have the more costly to produce blade bayonets. Has a 'trap door' style mechanism (also stainless steel) inside the stock that houses a complete cleaning kit (included).

It was assembled at Jianshe Arsenal in China during the era of Sino-Soviet cooperation (1956 roughly, exact manufacture date unknown), but using Russian parts and with Russian supervision. The rifle has Jianshe Arsenal stampings, but otherwise only Russian characters (no Chinese characters except the Jianshe Arsenal triangles). It is an all milled receiver (not stamped!). The stock is very interesting - it appears to be a harder wood than the "Chu wood" the Chinese typically used, perhaps of Russian origin. The stock also has some extensive trench art in it, including the initials "SD" and the word "POGRADEC," (a city in Albania) leading me to believe this rifle saw service in Albania. 

The rifle is unbelievably reliable, one of the nicest actions I have ever seen on an SKS. Everything operates smooth as silk. The bore is overall in good shape and was originally chrome lined. The rifling is in great shape and it's a great shooter. I have put 300 rounds through it, and have never once had a failure or malfunction of any kind, even with cheap steel case ammo. No failures to feed, to failures to eject, it just eats up and spits out anything you put in it. If you need a rifle that you KNOW will work, even if it's raining out and it's covered in mud, this is the rifle for you. Perfect hunting gun for the islands.

I will throw in about a dozen 7.62x39 stripper clips that I have verified to be the perfect size for feeding into this rifle. Will throw in a box of FMJ ammo as well.

The rifle is 100% legal and registered in my name, so the purchaser will have to meet me at the Wailuku Police Department to sign the rifle over (no cost I don't think, provided you have a permit to acquire rifles).

title: For Sale/Trade:  Technosight video archery range/simulator
postcontent: This is a Technohunt video screen archery simulator. This is not a cheap version from a catalog. This is one of those big systems that they have at your local archery range where you shoot at a screen with your bow and arrows and have to put on the special tips on your arrows and the computer scores your shot. There are leagues that use these throughout the year or random customers that pay by the session at the local archery shop to use this system. I will try to explain everything as much as I can. I acquired this system from a guy that had an archery shop that went out of business and he packed it away in boxes and it sat there for a while. I thought I would buy about the same time a friend of mine was buying a house that we could set it up in. Unfortunately, his house will not accommodate this system so I am selling it. I contacted technosight and talked to a very friendly sales person that explained the system to me. This is an approximately early 2000's timeframe model. It was what she called a "wintress" model. It has a laserdisc player with remote, 15 different laser discs with different shooting/hunting scenarios, a projector to project the video on the large white folded screen, instruction books, software, two boston acoustic speakers, a bunch of cables, brackets for the projector, extra bulbs for the projector, the sensors that you mount to the wall to track your shot. This system does not have the computer or the frame for the screen. The frame for the screen can be built out of wood by anyone that is fairly knowledgeable with tools. The computer I have seen on ebay for about 100 dollars. My research shows it used a dell optiplex 300 computer. Since I have not had the opportunity to install/test this system out due to lack of an area to do so, I have not had the chance to play with it and install it, etc. However, the system originally sold for about 18,000 dollars and was on sale at the AMO archery show for about 15,000 dollars back when it was new. Someone could install at there archery shop and charge for the hour or half hour, or perhaps install in a large trailer and charge by the shot at a sports show. I talked with the sales rep and just the screen is about 500 dollars new and the tips for the arrows are about 50 dollars for a small package. I can give you contact info for technosight and the person that fixes and repairs these systems in Michigan. I hope I am describing everything the best I can. I can try to answer questions the best I can during the time of the auction. Any questions, just let me know.

title: For Sale:  NEW LaRue Tactical PredatOBR 18" LT UDE .308 762
postcontent:
Larue Tactical PredatOBR with an 18 inch field grade barrel and UDE (Urban Dark Earth) furniture (stock and grip).

LaRue Tactical PredatOBR™ 7.62 
The PredatOBR 7.62 was designed for those who are searching for a hybrid cross between the standard OBR and PredatAR 7.62x51 Rifles. The PredatOBR takes the highly accurate OBR 7.62 design, and lightens it in every possible way with the least-possible impact to the accuracy that the standard OBR is known for. 

The most remarkable feature of the PredatOBR is its ability to be completely “broken down” and stored into the supplied Roll-Bag and Tool Box. The PredatOBR handguard has a locking stainless steel QD Lever system on each side. Once the levers are released, the handguard slides off of the upper assembly in seconds. The PredatOBR's barrel can easily be removed with the supplied PredatOBR Barrel Wrench, unscrew the Barrel Nut from Receiver and pull the Barrel Assembly free from Receiver. No need to remove the gas tube, gas block or muzzle device. Reverse the process to reinstall. Hand-tighten Barrel Nut and torque approximately 1/8-turn past hand-tight (Approximately 40-50 foot pounds). Once reassembled correctly, the point of impact (POI) shift will be 0.0 to 0.5 MOA of the original.

PredatOBR barrels are chambered in 7.62x51mm, and feature rifling in a 1/11.25 twist rate. All barrels are threaded in 5/8 x 24. Like the OBR and PredatAR riles, LaRue has eliminated the conventional AR barrel nut and bolt the handguard directly to the proprietary upper receiver, creating a true “free-float” barrel. The handguard does not touch the barrel or barrel nut at any place. The zero-MOA upper rail provides plenty of room for weapon-mounted night-vision day/night combinations. Both the upper and lower are CNC-machined from billet aluminum for the optimum fit and consistency. Even though it has been lightened certain features, there is still additional material in strategic areas to achieve maximum accuracy. 

The PredatOBR has threaded stainless-steel hard-points over the entire length of the handguard at the 3, 6, and 9 o’clock positions. These hard-points have an integral spine built-in for structural support. Provided with the system are three 3-inch MIL-STD-1913 rail sections that can be positioned anywhere along the handguard, per operator preference. These rail sections are attachable/detachable using a supplied tool (Torx® T-15 wrench). The rail sections are CNC-machined from billet aluminum. This robust solution provides a perfect precision mounting space for aiming lasers, illumination and bipods.

The PredatOBR's Port Selector Technology™ (PST) gas block is adjustable, to aid in the optimum function when using a sound suppressor. This special gas block contains a dual port mechanism that is operated by rotating a lever from one side to another. When the lever is rotated to the right-side of the rifle, the gasses are reduced, to compensate for the extra blowback created by the suppressor. When rotated to the left side, the gasses are increased for use without a suppressor.

The LaRue Tactical 6-position Retract Action Trigger (R.A.T.) Stock comes standard with every PredatOBR. It is ergonomic, has protected control surfaces and contains a set of cleaning rods in an internal compartment. Since the height of the 12 o’clock rail is at the optimum position, there is no need for a cheek riser as part of this system.

Specifications:
Caliber: 7.62 x 51 mm NATO 
Barrel Lengths: 14.5”,16.1”and 18” 
Rifling Twist Rate: 1/11.25 
Barrel Life: 10,000 (approx) 
Gas System: Direct Impingement with LaRue PST™ port selector 

Accessories: 
2ea, 20-Round Pmag Magazines
3ea 3” Rail Sections
Operators Manual
Carrying Case “Toolbox”
Roll-Up Cloth Case
Barrel Wrench

Suppressor Compatibility:
LaRue 7.62 rifles with Port Selector Technology (PST) have been optimized for best-performance with SureFire suppressors. We understand that there are dozens of 7.62 suppressors to choose from on the market at this time. We feel that SureFire suppressors fall somewhere in the middle-range in regards to effect of performance with gas-operated rifles. Many users have met with success operating different models of their choice. Combined with variables in ammunition, 7.62 suppressor owners have experienced a large spectrum of conditions (much greater than seen with 5.56 suppressors). This range of variables is easy to manage with a bolt-action 7.62, but with a gas-operated system it is not. While we made a concerted effort to design a gas system that will work with a wide range of suppressors, we can not guarantee proper-function with suppressor hardware other than SureFire.

About the “Black Gold” Trigger:
We are very proud to announce that we’ve selected the American Trigger Corporation AR Gold trigger to be installed in LaRue PredatOBRs going forward. These are a single stage trigger with take-up and a super short reset, similar in feel to a best-grade 1911 trigger, providing the optimum trigger action for a wide variety of shooting styles and disciplines. AR Gold Triggers have been used by some of the best competition shooters in the world for the last few years and dominate the top of the 3 Gun competition world. 

We have been testing and evaluating these triggers for well over a year, to ensure that they're up to our standard of quality. Our evaluation has shown the AR Gold to be magnificent and we're proud to include them as part of our new product line. One thing that is unusual about these triggers installed in our LaRue PredatOBRs, is they are treated with an IonBond black instead of American Trigger’s normal IonBond Gold. This is a custom color that is only available on LaRue Tactical rifles.

His wife left all 20 of his gorgeous and rare old smiths untouched and un-oiled for the following 20 years until current. It has no nicks and dings and it has a pretty nice finish on it's right or passenger side. But it's got a fair bit of light pitting on the left side. So what we have here is a gun that books at $1200-1400 easily in it's configuration if it weren't pitted. I don't know how to fix this other than polish and blast it back down and reblue it. And while that might fix the finish, it would obviously take it value down and that's why I've priced it as I have. It would make a VERY high end truck gun or house gun. These guns are hard to find and especially in the target version. This was an unfired gun as well, do despite it's freckling on the drivers side, it locks up tight as a bank vault, has a virginal bore and almost no "line" on the cylinder at all. This is the version with the ultra wide and deeply checkered hammer and trigger. It's action is light and breaks like glass like many of the fine old smith wheelguns. Adjustable sights. This is also the better built Pinned and recessed barrel and cylinder model. Has original serialized blue box, wax paper, manual and wood "football" grips that it came originally with and tools. Also comes with brand new Hogue tamer fingergroove grips as well. No Trades. Cash only. $525

postcontent:
Brand new, Never fired, Custom CMMG AR 15 with 16 inch bull barrel, RKM15 Keymod Free Float Handguard, Raptor Charging Handle, with a Nikon P223 scope mounted.  It also comes with 3-PMags, 1-Poly Mag, 60-steel case rounds, 60 brass rounds, and a blackhawk tactical carry bag.  The handguards are versatile an ready for you to customize to your liking.  Go to CMMGINC.com to see how you can personalize it.

Caliber: 5.56x45mm NATO Chamber 
Barrel: 16" Bull Barrel, WASP Treated 4140 Chrome-Moly Steel, 1:9" Twist 

W.A.S.P. Treated Barrel
(Weapon Armament Surface Protection) is a salt bath ferritic nitrocarburizing surface conversion process or more commonly referred to as nitriding. The nitriding conversion is applied to the barrel inside and out, along with the front sight base on our LE rifles and uppers. Nitriding offers improved wear, abrasion, and corrosion resistance when compared to hard chrome lining or phosphating. 

Unlike chrome lining, where the chrome is built up on the surface, nitriding converts the surface without the risk of dimensional build up. CMMG Pioneered the use of this nitriding process on AR barrels and has been using it for many years.
